article.headline: Arkansas State earns 100-86 victory over Alcorn State
article.description: — Dyondre Dominguez had 18 points in Arkansas State's 100-86 victory against Alcorn State on Tuesday.
article.linkText: Arkansas State earns 100-86 victory over Alcorn State
article.story: JONESBORO, Ark. -- — Dyondre Dominguez had 18 points in Arkansas State's 100-86 victory against Alcorn State on Tuesday. Dominguez added nine rebounds for the Red Wolves (1-2). Taryn Todd scored 17 points while shooting 5 for 13 (3 for 7 from 3-point range) and 4 of 4 from the free throw line. Freddy Hicks had 14 points and shot 5 for 8 (1 for 4 from 3-point range) and 3 of 4 from the free throw line. Jeremiah Kendall led the way for the Braves (1-2) with 28 points, 14 rebounds and two steals. Alcorn State also got 13 points and two steals from Jalen Hawkins. In addition, Mike Pajeaud had 12 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
